Experiment 37

This experiment allowed some small loans to originate with minimal verification.
Experiment started: 2016-12-13
26,148 treated applications and 25,658 control applications

res <- dbSendQuery(hbrstudy,"select 
                                 a.name,
                                 a.description,
                                 a.created_at,
                                 b.experiment_id,
                                 b.experimentable_id,
                                 b.experimentable_type,
                                 b.treatment,
                                 c.decision_status,
                                 c.raising_amount,
                                 c.created_at as appdate,
                                 c.number_of_dependents,
                                 c.selected_contract_years,
                                 c.use_of_funds,
                                  d.in_school,
                                  d.selected_loan_contract_id,
                                  d.equifax_credit_report_id,
                                  d.contract_type,d.upstart_application_id,
                                  d.user_account_id,
                                  e.annual_income,
                                  e.credit_report_id,
                                  e.dti,
                                  e.pricing_id,
                                  e.default_probability_coefficients,
                                  e.qualified_for_pricing,
                                  f.get_fico_score as ficoatorigination,
                                  f.at36_months_since_most_recent_delinquency as months_since_delinquency,
                                  f.bc101s_total_balance_of_all_credit_card_trades_verified_in_past_12_months as credit_card_balance_12_months,
                                  f.individual_credit_history_days,
                                  f.monthly_mortgage,
                                  f.mortgage_balance as init_mortgage_balance,
                                  f.num_inquiries_past_6_months,
                                  f.number_of_personal_loans,
                                  f.s002_birthdate_yymm_or_e_yy as dob,
                                  f.total_monthly_payments_excluding_mortgage,
                                  f.total_num_open_accounts,
                                  g.pricing_reason,
                                  h.id as final_acceptance_id,
                                  h.loan_contract_id,
                                  h.origination_date,
                                  h.status,
                                  h.client_ip,
                                  i.apr,
                                  i.contract_years,
                                  i.origination_fee_amount,
                                  i.monthly_payment,
                                  i.default_probability as defaultprob1,
                                  j.loan_amount,
                                  j.default_probability,
                                  j.apr_from_model,
                                  j.expected_cumulative_loss
                                 from monolith.experiments as a 
                                 LEFT JOIN monolith.experiment_memberships as b
                                 on a.id=b.experiment_id
                                 LEFT JOIN monolith.upstart_applications as c
                                 on b.experimentable_id = c.id
                                  LEFT JOIN monolith.user_applications as d 
                                  on c.id = d.upstart_application_id
                                  LEFT JOIN monolith.pricing_outputs as e
                                  on c.selected_pricing_output_id = e.id
                                  LEFT JOIN transunion.credit_reports as f
                                  on e.credit_report_id = f.id
                                  LEFT JOIN monolith.pricings as g
                                  on c.selected_pricing_output_id = g.selected_pricing_output_id
                                  LEFT JOIN monolith.final_acceptances as h
                                  on h.upstart_application_id = c.id
                                  LEFT JOIN monolith.loan_contracts as i
                                  on i.id = c.selected_loan_contract_id
                                  LEFT JOIN monolith.contract_pricings as j
                                  on j.loan_contract_id = i.id
                                where a.id=37")
exp37 <- dbFetch(res, n=-1)
dbClearResult(res)

exp37 <- data.table(exp37)


exp37[,approved:=ifelse(exp37$decision_status %in% c("funded","declined","rejected_funding") | exp37$status %in% c("final_accepted","prepublish_accepted"),1,0)]



exp37[,appdate:=as.Date(exp37$appdate)]
exp37[,applicationyear:=year(appdate)]
exp37[,daystooriginate:=as.numeric(exp37$origination_date-exp37$appdate)]

Descriptive statsitics: Treatment vs Control Samples

  • Approval rate is significantly higher in treatment sample (99 pct vs 79 pct)
  • 75 pct of treated applications approved within 2 days; 75 pct of control applications approved within 7 days
  • Other characteristics are very similar
summary = by(exp37[,c("treatment","approved","default_probability","ficoatorigination","loan_amount","apr","contract_years","init_mortgage_balance","num_inquiries_past_6_months","individual_credit_history_days","origination_fee_amount","daystooriginate","annual_income","qualified_for_pricing","applicationyear")], exp37$treatment, stargazer, type = 'text')

Regression: Pr(Approval) on treatment

  • treated applications 20 pct more likely to be approved
reg <- felm(approved~treatment+ficoatorigination+log(1+annual_income)+log(1+init_mortgage_balance)+num_inquiries_past_6_months+individual_credit_history_days|applicationyear,data=exp37)

printtable(reg,lines=list(c("FE","Year")))

Exp37 loan performance

res <- dbSendQuery(hbrstudy,"
                   select 
                   a.final_acceptance_id,
                   a.as_of_date,
                   a.days_past_due,
                   a.loan_status,
                   a.seasoning_in_months
                   from monolith.daily_loan_snapshots as a
                   LEFT JOIN monolith.final_acceptances as b
                   on a.final_acceptance_id = b.id
                   where b.id in (
                          select p.id
                          from monolith.final_acceptances as p
                          LEFT JOIN monolith.upstart_applications as q
                          on q.id = p.upstart_application_id
                          LEFT JOIN monolith.experiment_memberships as r
                          on q.id = r.experimentable_id
                          LEFT JOIN monolith.experiments as s
                          on s.id = r.experiment_id
                          where s.id=37)")
exp37per <- dbFetch(res, n=-1)
dbClearResult(res)

exp37per <- data.table(exp37per)
exp37per[,charged_off:=ifelse(loan_status %in% c("charged_off","partially_charged_off"),1,0)]
exp37per[,delinquent:=ifelse(loan_status %in% c("charged_off","partially_charged_off","delinquent"),1,0)]

exp37sum <- exp37per[,.(charged_off=mean(charged_off,na.rm=TRUE),delinquent=mean(delinquent,na.rm=TRUE)),by=final_acceptance_id]

exp37sum[,charged_off:=ifelse(charged_off>0,1,0)]
exp37sum[,delinquent:=ifelse(delinquent>0,1,0)]

exp37 = merge(exp37,exp37sum,by="final_acceptance_id",all.x = TRUE)

Regression: Delinquent on treatment

  • Treated loans are more likely to become delinquent
regs <- list()

regs[[3]] <- felm(delinquent~treatment|applicationyear,exp37)
regs[[4]] <- felm(delinquent~treatment+ficoatorigination+log(1+annual_income)+log(1+init_mortgage_balance)+num_inquiries_past_6_months+log(1+individual_credit_history_days)|applicationyear,exp37)

printtable(regs,lines = list(c("FE","Year","Year","Year","Year")),column.labels = c("charged off","charged off","delinquent","delinquent"))

Credit reports

res <- dbSendQuery(hbrstudy,"select 
                                  a.get_fico_score as fico,
                                  a.num_inquiries_past_6_months,
                                  a.created_at,
                                  a.at36_months_since_most_recent_delinquency as months_since_delinquency,
                                  a.bc101s_total_balance_of_all_credit_card_trades_verified_in_past_12_months as credit_card_balance_12_months,
                                  a.individual_credit_history_days,
                                  a.monthly_mortgage,
                                  a.mortgage_balance,
                                  a.number_of_personal_loans,
                                  a.total_monthly_payments_excluding_mortgage,
                                  a.total_num_open_accounts,
                                  a.num_trades_currently_delinquent,
                                  a.open_personal_loan_balance,
                                  a.at02s_number_of_open_trades,
                                  a.at05_number_of_trades_opened_in_past_3_months,
                                  a.au01s_number_of_auto_trades,
                                  a.au06s_number_of_auto_trades_opened_in_past_6_months,
                                  a.bc107s_number_of_30_and_60_days_past_due_ratings_on_credit_card_trades,
                                  a.bc108s_number_of_90_or_more_days_past_due_ratings_on_credit_card_trades,
                                  b.credit_report_id,
                                  b.user_account_id
                              from transunion.credit_reports as a
                              LEFT JOIN monolith.credit_report_summaries as b
                              on b.credit_report_id = a.id
                              where b.user_account_id in
                                (select p.user_account_id from monolith.user_applications as p
                                LEFT JOIN monolith.upstart_applications as q
                                on q.id = p.upstart_application_id
                                LEFT JOIN monolith.experiment_memberships as r
                                on r.experimentable_id = q.id
                                LEFT JOIN monolith.experiments as s
                                on s.id = r.experiment_id
                                where s.id=37)")


creditreports37 <- dbFetch(res, n=-1)
dbClearResult(res)

creditreports37 <- data.table(creditreports37)
creditreports37[,created_at:=as.Date(created_at)]

creditreports37 <- creditreports37[!is.na(fico)]
creditreports37 <- creditreports37[!duplicated(credit_report_id)]
creditreports37 <- creditreports37[!duplicated(creditreports37[,c("created_at","user_account_id")])]

creditreports37[,creditcarddelinq:=bc107s_number_of_30_and_60_days_past_due_ratings_on_credit_card_trades + bc108s_number_of_90_or_more_days_past_due_ratings_on_credit_card_trades]


creditreportcount <- creditreports37[,.(count=.N,mindate=min(created_at),maxdate=max(created_at)),by=user_account_id]

creditreports37 <- merge(creditreports37,exp37[,c("user_account_id","approved","treatment","appdate","applicationyear","use_of_funds","init_mortgage_balance","selected_contract_years","ficoatorigination","raising_amount")],by="user_account_id")

creditreports37 <- creditreports37[appdate<=created_at]

creditreports37[,monthssinceapp:=round(as.numeric(created_at - appdate)/(365.25/12))]
creditreports37[,year:=year(created_at)]
creditreports37[,mortgage:=ifelse(mortgage_balance>0,1,0)]

Subsequent availability of credit reports

  • Why is there a spike in 12 months for loans not approved?
monthsummary <- creditreports37[,.N,by=.(approved,treatment,monthssinceapp)]
monthsummary[,cat:=paste("approved = ",monthsummary$approved,"& treatment =",monthsummary$treatment)]

ggplot(monthsummary[monthssinceapp<36],aes(x=monthssinceapp,y=log(N),color=cat)) + geom_line()

Regressions: Impact of treatment on future financial condition

  • FICO score of treated applicants drop
  • Treated applicants have more loans in the first year. i.e.credit constraints binding?
  • Treated applicants are more likely to default on credit cards
  • Treated applicants are less likely to purchase a home
  • Treated applicants are less likely to purchase a new vehicle
regs <- list()

regs[[1]] <- felm(fico~treatment*factor(monthssinceapp)+selected_contract_years+ficoatorigination+log(raising_amount)|year+applicationyear+use_of_funds|0|applicationyear,data=creditreports37[monthssinceapp<=30 ])
regs[[2]] <- felm(number_of_personal_loans~treatment*factor(monthssinceapp)+selected_contract_years+ficoatorigination+log(raising_amount)|year+applicationyear+use_of_funds|0|applicationyear,data=creditreports37[monthssinceapp<=30 ])
regs[[3]] <- felm(creditcarddelinq~treatment*factor(monthssinceapp)+selected_contract_years+ficoatorigination+log(raising_amount)|year+applicationyear+use_of_funds|0|applicationyear,data=creditreports37[monthssinceapp<=30 ])
regs[[4]] <- felm(mortgage~treatment*factor(monthssinceapp)+selected_contract_years+ficoatorigination+log(raising_amount)|year+applicationyear+use_of_funds|0|applicationyear,data=creditreports37[monthssinceapp<=30 &  init_mortgage_balance==0])
regs[[5]] <- felm(au06s_number_of_auto_trades_opened_in_past_6_months~treatment*factor(monthssinceapp)+selected_contract_years+ficoatorigination+log(raising_amount)|year+applicationyear+use_of_funds|0|applicationyear,data=creditreports37[monthssinceapp<=30 ])

# printtable(regs)

gr <- list()

gr[[4]] <- coef_plot_1reg(regs[[4]],"treatmentTRUE:factor(monthssinceapp)",0)+ggtitle("Home purchase")

Upstarts decision to drop the minimum FICO score requirement to 620 from 640 in July 2016 as an experiment

res <- dbSendQuery(hbrstudy,"
            select 
              a.created_at,
              a.decision_status, 
              a.selected_contract_years, 
              a.use_of_funds, 
              b.raising_amount, 
              b.upstart_application_id,
              c.annual_income,
              c.dti,
              d.get_fico_score as ficoatorigination,
              b.user_account_id,
              f.pricing_reason
            from monolith.upstart_applications as a 
            LEFT JOIN monolith.user_applications as b 
            on a.id = b.upstart_application_id
            LEFT JOIN monolith.pricing_outputs as c
            on a.selected_pricing_output_id = c.id
            LEFT JOIN transunion.credit_reports as d
            on c.credit_report_id = d.id
            LEFT JOIN monolith.pricings as f
            on a.selected_pricing_output_id = f.selected_pricing_output_id
            where a.created_at > '2015-01-01' and a.created_at < '2017-12-31' and ficoatorigination<700")
apps640 <- dbFetch(res, n=-1)
dbClearResult(res)

apps640 <- data.table(apps640)

apps640[,created_at:=as.Date(apps640$created_at)]

apps640[,applicationmonth:=as.Date(paste0(substr(as.character(apps640$created_at),1,7),"-01"))]

apps640[,year:=year(apps640$created_at)]

apps640[,approved:=ifelse(apps640$decision_status %in% c("funded","failed_to_fund"),1,0)]

apps640[,analyticsample:=ifelse(apps640$decision_status %in% c("funded","failed_to_fund","disqualified"),1,0)]

apps640[,fico10bin:=floor(apps640$ficoatorigination/10)*10]

apps640[,ficoless640:=ifelse(apps640$ficoatorigination<640,1,0)]

apps640[,afterJune2016:= ifelse(apps640$applicationmonth>="2016-06-01",1,0)]

apps640 <- apps640[!is.na(apps640$ficoatorigination)]

  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = 640), colour="red")+

Fraction of approved loans with FICO less than 640

less640 = apps640[apps640$approved==1 & !is.na(apps640$ficoatorigination),.N,by=.(applicationmonth,ficoless640)]

less640 = dcast(less640,applicationmonth~ficoless640,fun.aggregate = sum)

names(less640) = c("month","more","less")

less640 = data.table(less640)
less640[,fracless640:=less640$less/(less640$less+less640$more)]

ggplot(less640,aes(x=month,y=fracless640))+geom_line()+theme_minimal()+geom_vline(aes(xintercept = as.Date("2016-06-01")), colour="red")

Probability of Approval when FICO is less than 640

approvalpct = apps640[apps640$ficoless640==1 & !is.na(apps640$ficoatorigination),.(approvalfrac=mean(approved,na.rm=TRUE)),by=.(applicationmonth)]

ggplot(approvalpct,aes(x=applicationmonth,y=approvalfrac))+geom_line()+theme_minimal()+geom_vline(aes(xintercept = as.Date("2016-06-01")), colour="red")

res <- dbSendQuery(hbrstudy,"
            select 
                a.get_fico_score as fico,
                a.num_inquiries_past_6_months,
                a.created_at,
                a.at36_months_since_most_recent_delinquency as months_since_delinquency,
                a.bc101s_total_balance_of_all_credit_card_trades_verified_in_past_12_months as credit_card_balance_12_months,
                a.individual_credit_history_days,
                a.monthly_mortgage,
                a.mortgage_balance,
                a.number_of_personal_loans,
                a.total_monthly_payments_excluding_mortgage,
                a.total_num_open_accounts,
                a.num_trades_currently_delinquent,
                a.open_personal_loan_balance,
                a.at02s_number_of_open_trades,
                a.at05_number_of_trades_opened_in_past_3_months,
                a.au01s_number_of_auto_trades,
                a.au06s_number_of_auto_trades_opened_in_past_6_months,
                a.bc107s_number_of_30_and_60_days_past_due_ratings_on_credit_card_trades,
                a.bc108s_number_of_90_or_more_days_past_due_ratings_on_credit_card_trades,
                b.credit_report_id,
                b.user_account_id
            from transunion.credit_reports as a
            LEFT JOIN monolith.credit_report_summaries as b
            on b.credit_report_id = a.id
            where b.user_account_id in
            (select 
            b.user_account_id
            from monolith.upstart_applications as a 
            LEFT JOIN monolith.user_applications as b 
            on a.id = b.upstart_application_id
            LEFT JOIN monolith.pricing_outputs as c
            on a.selected_pricing_output_id = c.id
            LEFT JOIN transunion.credit_reports as d
            on c.credit_report_id = d.id
            where a.created_at > '2015-01-01' and a.created_at < '2017-12-31' 
            and d.get_fico_score<700)")
creditreports640 <- dbFetch(res, n=-1)
dbClearResult(res)

creditreports640 <- data.table(creditreports640)
creditreports640[,created_at:=as.Date(created_at)]

creditreports640 <- creditreports640[!is.na(fico)]
creditreports640 <- creditreports640[!duplicated(credit_report_id)]
creditreports640 <- creditreports640[!duplicated(creditreports640[,c("created_at","user_account_id")])]

creditreports640[,creditcarddelinq:=bc107s_number_of_30_and_60_days_past_due_ratings_on_credit_card_trades + bc108s_number_of_90_or_more_days_past_due_ratings_on_credit_card_trades]


creditreportcount <- creditreports640[,.(count=.N,mindate=min(created_at),maxdate=max(created_at)),by=user_account_id]


creditreports640 <- merge(creditreports640,apps640[,c("user_account_id","approved","decision_status","use_of_funds","raising_amount","annual_income","applicationmonth","ficoatorigination","selected_contract_years","afterJune2016","ficoless640")],by="user_account_id")

creditreports640[,mortgage:=ifelse(mortgage_balance>0,1,0)]

Regressions: Impact of treatment on future financial condition

What explains the breaks in following graphs? Particularly around 12th month and 24th month.

  • FICO score of treated applicants drop
  • Treated applicants are more likely to default on credit cards
  • Treated applicants are less likely to purchase a home
  • Treated applicants are less likely to purchase a new vehicle
regs <- list()

regs[[1]] <- felm(fico~afterJune2016*factor(monthssinceapp)+ficoatorigination+log(raising_amount)|0|0|applicationmonth,data=creditreports640[monthssinceapp<=30 & ficoatorigination<640])
regs[[2]] <- felm(number_of_personal_loans~afterJune2016*factor(monthssinceapp)+ficoatorigination+log(raising_amount)|0|0|applicationmonth,data=creditreports640[monthssinceapp<=30 & ficoatorigination<640])
regs[[3]] <- felm(creditcarddelinq~afterJune2016*factor(monthssinceapp)+ficoatorigination+log(raising_amount)|0|0|applicationmonth,data=creditreports640[monthssinceapp<=30 & ficoatorigination<640])
regs[[4]] <- felm(mortgage~afterJune2016*factor(monthssinceapp)+ficoatorigination+log(raising_amount)|0|0|applicationmonth,data=creditreports640[monthssinceapp<=30 & ficoatorigination<640 ])
regs[[5]] <- felm(au06s_number_of_auto_trades_opened_in_past_6_months~afterJune2016*factor(monthssinceapp)+ficoatorigination+log(raising_amount)|0|0|applicationmonth,data=creditreports640[monthssinceapp<=30 & ficoatorigination<640])


gr <- list()
gr[[1]] <- coef_plot_1reg(regs[[1]],"afterJune2016:factor(monthssinceapp)",0)+ggtitle("FICO")
gr[[2]] <- coef_plot_1reg(regs[[2]],"afterJune2016:factor(monthssinceapp)",0)+ggtitle("# personal loans")
gr[[3]] <- coef_plot_1reg(regs[[3]],"afterJune2016:factor(monthssinceapp)",0)+ggtitle("Credit card delinquency")
gr[[4]] <- coef_plot_1reg(regs[[4]],"afterJune2016:factor(monthssinceapp)",0)+ggtitle("Home purchase")
gr[[5]] <- coef_plot_1reg(regs[[5]],"afterJune2016:factor(monthssinceapp)",0)+ggtitle("New vehicle")

grid.arrange(gr[[1]],gr[[2]],gr[[3]],gr[[4]],gr[[5]],ncol=2)
